{
  "texts": [
    "These human losses occur predominantly in developing countries, and the consequent effects on businesses and the economy can be very significant (Brabhaharan et al. 2001).",
    "According to the CRED, in 2022, 387 natural hazards and disasters worldwide occurred, resulting in the loss of 30,704 lives and affecting 185 million individuals.",
    "Economic losses totaled around US$ 223.8 billion.",
    "The 2022 record is slightly higher than the average from 2002 to 2021 (370), and the occurrence of each type of disaster was also close to the average levels in the last two decades (CRED Crunch 2022).",
    "According to Fig. 1, between 2002 and 2022, America and Asia are the most affected continents by disasters, with economic losses amounting to 400 billion dollars (CRED 2022)."
  ]
}